      <description>&lt;p&gt;I am a 4th-year graduate student pursing Ph.D. degree in Division of Computer Science and Engineering at Louisiana State University, Baton Rouge. I am working in 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://csc.lsu.edu/~qywang/ProjectWebsite/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;LSU Cloud Computing Lab&lt;/a&gt; as a research assistant under 
&lt;a href=&#34;http://csc.lsu.edu/~qywang/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Dr. Qingyang Wang&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My interest lies in performance and scalability analysis of large-scale web applications and IoT stream processing systems, with the aim of achieving highly responsive systems running at high utilization in cloud. My research focuses on automated measurements and analysis of system performance and applying learning techniques to bring better scalability and elasticity in the cloud.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
